WEBVTT

00:01.625 --> 00:05.208
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

00:01.625 --> 00:05.208
<i>Stardate 43989.1.</i>

00:05.250 --> 00:07.834
<i>The</i> Enterprise<i> has arrived</i>

00:05.250 --> 00:07.834
<i>at Jouret IV</i>

00:07.875 --> 00:09.750
<i>in response</i>

00:07.875 --> 00:09.750
<i>to a distress signal</i>

00:09.792 --> 00:12.875
<i>from one of the Federation's</i>

00:09.792 --> 00:12.875
<i>outermost colonies.</i>

00:15.917 --> 00:17.875
Anything from the surface?

00:17.917 --> 00:19.959
No, sir. There have

00:17.917 --> 00:19.959
been no communications

00:20.000 --> 00:21.709
from the colony

00:20.000 --> 00:21.709
for over 12 hours.

00:21.750 --> 00:23.166
Sensors picking up

00:21.750 --> 00:23.166
any signs of life?

00:23.208 --> 00:24.375
None.

00:24.417 --> 00:25.417
The surface environment

00:25.458 --> 00:27.542
is safe for transport,

00:25.458 --> 00:27.542
Commander.

00:46.417 --> 00:47.917
Mr. O'Brien.

00:47.959 --> 00:50.041
Verify these are

00:47.959 --> 00:50.041
accurate coordinates

00:50.083 --> 00:52.000
for the New Providence colony.

00:52.041 --> 00:53.333
Coordinates verified, sir.

00:53.375 --> 00:55.625
You're at the center of town.

01:46.041 --> 01:50.458
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

01:50.500 --> 01:54.667
<i>These are the voyages</i>

01:50.500 --> 01:54.667
<i>of the Starship</i> Enterprise.

01:54.709 --> 01:56.583
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

01:56.625 --> 02:00.250
<i>to explore</i>

01:56.625 --> 02:00.250
<i>strange new worlds</i>

02:00.291 --> 02:04.500
<i>to seek out new life</i>

02:00.291 --> 02:04.500
<i>and new civilizations</i>

02:04.542 --> 02:09.375
<i>to boldly go</i>

02:04.542 --> 02:09.375
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

03:08.375 --> 03:11.583
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

03:08.375 --> 03:11.583
<i>Stardate 43992.6.</i>

03:11.625 --> 03:13.917
<i>Admiral Hanson and Lieutenant</i>

03:11.625 --> 03:13.917
<i>Commander Shelby</i>

03:13.959 --> 03:15.375
<i>of Starfleet Tactical</i>

03:15.417 --> 03:16.834
<i>have arrived to review</i>

03:15.417 --> 03:16.834
<i>the disappearance</i>

03:16.875 --> 03:18.291
<i>of New Providence colony.</i>

03:18.333 --> 03:21.792
<i>No sign remains</i>

03:18.333 --> 03:21.792
<i>of the 900 inhabitants.</i>

03:21.834 --> 03:24.000
The truth is...

03:24.041 --> 03:26.458
hell, we are not ready.

03:26.500 --> 03:29.667
We've known they were coming

03:26.500 --> 03:29.667
for over a year.

03:29.709 --> 03:31.792
We've thrown every resource we

03:29.709 --> 03:31.792
have into this, but still...

03:31.834 --> 03:33.083
RIKER:

03:31.834 --> 03:33.083
Then you're

03:31.834 --> 03:33.083
convinced

03:33.125 --> 03:34.125
it is the Borg.

03:34.166 --> 03:36.000
That's what I'm here

03:34.166 --> 03:36.000
to find out.

03:36.041 --> 03:38.500
The initial descriptions

03:36.041 --> 03:38.500
of the surface conditions

03:38.542 --> 03:41.375
are almost identical

03:38.542 --> 03:41.375
to your report from System J-25.

03:41.417 --> 03:42.917
Commander Riker

03:41.417 --> 03:42.917
wrote those reports.

03:42.959 --> 03:44.000
He agrees with you.

03:44.041 --> 03:45.375
Commander Shelby

03:45.417 --> 03:49.250
took over Borg tactical analysis

03:45.417 --> 03:49.250
six months ago.

03:49.291 --> 03:51.333
I've learned to give her

03:49.291 --> 03:51.333
a wide latitude

03:51.375 --> 03:53.458
when I want

03:51.375 --> 03:53.458
to get things done.

03:53.500 --> 03:56.458
That's how I intend

03:53.500 --> 03:56.458
to operate here.

03:56.500 --> 03:59.333
My priority has been

03:56.500 --> 03:59.333
to develop some kind--

03:59.375 --> 04:01.208
any kind--

03:59.375 --> 04:01.208
of defense strategy.

04:01.250 --> 04:03.750
Obviously, nothing we have now

04:01.250 --> 04:03.750
can stop them.

04:03.792 --> 04:05.417
We've been designing new weapons

04:05.458 --> 04:07.500
but they're all

04:05.458 --> 04:07.500
still on the drawing board.

04:07.542 --> 04:09.750
We expected much more lead time.

04:09.792 --> 04:11.667
Your encounter with the Borg

04:11.709 --> 04:13.959
was over 7,000

04:11.709 --> 04:13.959
light years away.

04:14.000 --> 04:15.375
If this<i> is</i> the Borg

04:15.417 --> 04:16.667
it would indicate they have

04:16.709 --> 04:19.250
a source of power

04:16.709 --> 04:19.250
far superior to our own.

04:19.291 --> 04:21.542
I'd like to see the colony site

04:19.291 --> 04:21.542
as soon as possible, Captain.

04:21.583 --> 04:22.959
It'll be dark there

04:21.583 --> 04:22.959
in 30 minutes.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.375
We've scheduled an away team

04:23.000 --> 04:24.375
for dawn.

04:24.417 --> 04:25.667
Number One,

04:24.417 --> 04:25.667
why don't you

04:25.709 --> 04:27.583
show the Commander

04:25.709 --> 04:27.583
to her quarters.

04:30.375 --> 04:32.375
It's our poker night,

04:30.375 --> 04:32.375
Admiral.

04:32.417 --> 04:35.083
There's always

04:32.417 --> 04:35.083
an open seat for you.

04:35.125 --> 04:37.083
Another time, Commander.

04:37.125 --> 04:39.250
Your Captain and I

04:37.125 --> 04:39.250
have a lot to cover.

04:39.291 --> 04:41.000
But, uh, rumor has it

04:41.041 --> 04:44.417
Commander Shelby has

04:41.041 --> 04:44.417
played a hand or two.

04:49.125 --> 04:51.709
Keep your eye on her, Jean-Luc.

04:51.750 --> 04:55.125
She's one very impressive

04:51.750 --> 04:55.125
young lady.

04:55.166 --> 04:57.625
You seem rather taken

04:55.166 --> 04:57.625
with her, J.P.

04:57.667 --> 05:00.375
Just an old man's fantasies.

05:02.083 --> 05:05.041
When Shelby came into Tactical,

05:02.083 --> 05:05.041
every admiral's uncle

05:05.083 --> 05:07.959
had a take

05:05.083 --> 05:07.959
on this Borg business.

05:08.000 --> 05:09.875
She cut through it.

05:09.917 --> 05:11.709
She put us on track.

05:13.291 --> 05:15.000
Earl Grey?

05:15.041 --> 05:16.500
Please.

05:16.542 --> 05:19.625
She'd make you one hell

05:16.542 --> 05:19.625
of a First Officer.

05:19.667 --> 05:22.333
Already have a hell

05:19.667 --> 05:22.333
of a First Officer.

05:22.375 --> 05:25.417
Don't tell me he's going

05:22.375 --> 05:25.417
to pass up another commission.

05:27.291 --> 05:28.583
One's available?

05:28.625 --> 05:29.959
The<i> Melbourne.</i>

05:30.000 --> 05:31.291
It's his if he wants it.

05:31.333 --> 05:32.500
Hasn't he told you?

05:34.000 --> 05:36.417
He'll make a fine captain, J.P.

05:38.166 --> 05:40.667
You may want to tell<i> him</i> that.

05:40.709 --> 05:43.041
We're still waiting

05:40.709 --> 05:43.041
on his decision.

05:43.083 --> 05:45.291
This is the third time

05:45.333 --> 05:48.375
we've pulled out

05:45.333 --> 05:48.375
the Captain's chair for Riker.

05:48.417 --> 05:51.417
He just won't sit down.

05:51.458 --> 05:53.542
Well, let me tell you something,

05:51.458 --> 05:53.542
Jean-Luc--

05:53.583 --> 05:56.542
there are a lot

05:53.583 --> 05:56.542
of young hotshots like Shelby

05:56.583 --> 05:57.959
on the way up.

05:58.000 --> 05:59.375
Riker could suddenly look

05:59.417 --> 06:02.291
like he's standing still

05:59.417 --> 06:02.291
next to them.

06:02.333 --> 06:04.875
He's hurting his career

06:02.333 --> 06:04.875
by staying put.

06:04.917 --> 06:07.166
And if I were you,

06:04.917 --> 06:07.166
I'd kick him in the rear end

06:07.208 --> 06:09.417
for his own good.

06:16.250 --> 06:18.750
I don't know exactly

06:16.250 --> 06:18.750
what I'm looking for

06:18.792 --> 06:21.208
but we've tested

06:18.792 --> 06:21.208
the sections of the

06:18.792 --> 06:21.208
<i>Enterprise's</i> hull

06:21.250 --> 06:22.792
that were damaged

06:21.250 --> 06:22.792
by the Borg.

06:22.834 --> 06:25.417
There were some unusual

06:22.834 --> 06:25.417
magnetic-resonance traces.

06:25.458 --> 06:27.333
A Borg footprint?

06:27.375 --> 06:29.041
That's my theory.

06:29.083 --> 06:31.041
I'll see if it holds up

06:29.083 --> 06:31.041
tomorrow.

06:31.083 --> 06:32.083
I've reviewed your personnel.

06:32.125 --> 06:33.625
I'll be assigning Mr. La Forge

06:33.667 --> 06:36.375
and Mr. Data

06:33.667 --> 06:36.375
to accompany me

06:33.667 --> 06:36.375
on the away team.

06:36.417 --> 06:39.792
I've already assigned them

06:36.417 --> 06:39.792
to the away team.

06:39.834 --> 06:42.375
And I'll be with you as well,

06:39.834 --> 06:42.375
Commander.

06:42.417 --> 06:43.875
Of course.

06:43.917 --> 06:46.583
I appreciate any assistance

06:43.917 --> 06:46.583
you can offer.

06:46.625 --> 06:48.875
Tell me, Commander.

06:48.917 --> 06:50.709
Is serving aboard the<i> Enterprise</i>

06:50.750 --> 06:53.000
as extraordinary an experience

06:50.750 --> 06:53.000
as I've heard?

06:53.041 --> 06:54.875
Every bit.

06:54.917 --> 06:58.875
Good, because I intend

06:54.917 --> 06:58.875
to convince Captain Picard

06:58.917 --> 07:00.834
that I'm the right choice

06:58.917 --> 07:00.834
for the job.

07:00.875 --> 07:02.917
Job? Which job?

07:02.959 --> 07:04.875
Yours, of course.

07:06.542 --> 07:09.333
I'm sorry.

07:09.375 --> 07:11.625
I heard that you were leaving.

07:11.667 --> 07:16.709
If I were, I'm sure

07:11.667 --> 07:16.709
you'd be the first to know.

07:19.125 --> 07:24.583
Poker's at 1700 hours

07:19.125 --> 07:24.583
in my quarters, deck eight.

07:28.667 --> 07:30.667
Got another king

07:28.667 --> 07:30.667
in the hole, eh, Data?

07:30.709 --> 07:33.208
I am afraid I cannot

07:30.709 --> 07:33.208
answer that, Wesley

07:33.250 --> 07:35.000
and as you are a

07:33.250 --> 07:35.000
newcomer to the game

07:35.041 --> 07:37.750
may I say, it is

07:35.041 --> 07:37.750
inappropriate

07:35.041 --> 07:37.750
for you to ask.

07:37.792 --> 07:39.458
(<i> players chuckle</i> )

07:39.500 --> 07:41.667
I will buy

07:39.500 --> 07:41.667
another card, Counselor.

07:41.709 --> 07:44.291
No help there.

07:44.333 --> 07:47.291
Fold. Again.

07:47.333 --> 07:50.667
Three jacks looking back

07:47.333 --> 07:50.667
for the handsome young ensign.

07:50.709 --> 07:53.792
Pair of deuces stands.

07:53.834 --> 07:57.417
Flush, possible

07:53.834 --> 07:57.417
straight flush.

07:57.458 --> 07:58.959
Hmm.

07:59.000 --> 08:01.083
Your bet, Mr. Crusher.

08:03.917 --> 08:05.250
I'm in for ten.

08:05.291 --> 08:06.959
Call.

08:07.000 --> 08:09.166
Now it's time

08:07.000 --> 08:09.166
for the long pants.

08:09.208 --> 08:12.000
There's your ten. 100.

08:12.041 --> 08:13.667
He's got the straight

08:12.041 --> 08:13.667
flush, folks.

08:13.709 --> 08:15.333
Not necessarily.

08:15.375 --> 08:18.542
Commander Riker

08:15.375 --> 08:18.542
may be bluffing, Wesley.

08:23.500 --> 08:25.667
I don't think so.

08:23.500 --> 08:25.667
Fold.

08:25.709 --> 08:27.750
With three jacks?

08:25.709 --> 08:27.750
What, are you kidding?

08:27.792 --> 08:29.458
Wesley, you may get

08:27.792 --> 08:29.458
straight A's in school

08:29.500 --> 08:32.000
but there's a lot you

08:29.500 --> 08:32.000
need to learn about poker.

08:34.041 --> 08:37.291
Well, I've only got two pair

08:37.333 --> 08:40.333
but I've got to see

08:37.333 --> 08:40.333
your hole card.

08:40.375 --> 08:42.709
I'll call.

08:46.417 --> 08:49.875
(<i> Geordi chuckles</i> )

08:49.917 --> 08:52.291
You got him.

09:09.417 --> 09:11.709
Mr. Data and our guest

09:09.417 --> 09:11.709
appear to be tardy.

09:11.750 --> 09:13.834
Sir, Commander Shelby

09:11.750 --> 09:13.834
and Data beamed down

09:13.875 --> 09:15.625
to the planet's

09:13.875 --> 09:15.625
surface an hour ago.

09:15.667 --> 09:17.333
On whose authority?

09:17.375 --> 09:19.417
On hers, sir.

09:38.834 --> 09:39.959
Morning.

09:40.000 --> 09:41.834
Early bird gets

09:40.000 --> 09:41.834
the worm, eh?

09:41.875 --> 09:45.375
We've had some

09:41.875 --> 09:45.375
interesting results.

09:45.417 --> 09:47.709
Commander Shelby...

09:49.625 --> 09:52.041
Walk with me, Commander.

10:00.375 --> 10:01.959
Early bird?

10:02.000 --> 10:04.583
I believe

10:02.000 --> 10:04.583
Commander Shelby erred.

10:04.625 --> 10:06.458
There is no evidence

10:04.625 --> 10:06.458
of avifaunal

10:06.500 --> 10:08.875
or crawling vermicular

10:06.500 --> 10:08.875
life-forms on Jouret IV.

10:08.917 --> 10:11.291
That's not what

10:08.917 --> 10:11.291
she meant, Data

10:11.333 --> 10:14.834
but you're right--

10:11.333 --> 10:14.834
she erred.

10:18.583 --> 10:20.166
I'm sorry,

10:18.583 --> 10:20.166
but I woke up early

10:20.208 --> 10:22.208
and I saw that a weather

10:20.208 --> 10:22.208
system was moving in.

10:22.250 --> 10:23.834
It could have affected

10:22.250 --> 10:23.834
the soil readings.

10:23.875 --> 10:25.166
So without any regard

10:25.208 --> 10:26.750
for the risk of coming

10:25.208 --> 10:26.750
down here alone...

10:26.792 --> 10:29.291
Really, Commander,

10:26.792 --> 10:29.291
if we ran into the Borg here

10:29.333 --> 10:31.250
two extra bodies wouldn't have

10:29.333 --> 10:31.250
made a hell of a difference

10:31.291 --> 10:32.583
now, would they?

10:32.625 --> 10:34.583
We had three hours

10:32.625 --> 10:34.583
before the storm front hit

10:34.625 --> 10:35.959
less than two hours now.

10:36.000 --> 10:37.291
Data was available.

10:37.333 --> 10:38.583
I took him.

10:37.333 --> 10:38.583
We came.

10:38.625 --> 10:40.125
I don't see your problem.

10:40.166 --> 10:42.667
My problem, Commander, is

10:40.166 --> 10:42.667
I expect to be notified

10:42.709 --> 10:44.625
before there's a

10:42.709 --> 10:44.625
change in my orders.

10:44.667 --> 10:46.458
Noted for future reference.

10:46.500 --> 10:48.625
Do you wish to hear

10:46.500 --> 10:48.625
my report, sir?

10:48.667 --> 10:50.583
Go ahead.

10:50.625 --> 10:53.750
The soil contains the same

10:50.625 --> 10:53.750
magnetic-resonance traces.

10:53.792 --> 10:55.625
That's our footprint.

10:55.667 --> 10:57.333
There's no doubt anymore.

10:57.375 --> 10:59.417
It is the Borg.

11:03.917 --> 11:07.375
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

11:03.917 --> 11:07.375
<i>Stardate 43993.5.</i>

11:07.417 --> 11:10.250
<i>With confirmation of the Borg's</i>

11:07.417 --> 11:10.250
presence in Federation space

11:10.291 --> 11:12.834
<i>Admiral Hanson has returned</i>

11:10.291 --> 11:12.834
<i>to Starbase 324</i>

11:12.875 --> 11:15.417
<i>to discuss strategy</i>

11:12.875 --> 11:15.417
<i>with Starfleet Command.</i>

11:15.458 --> 11:17.834
<i>Lieutenant Commander Shelby</i>

11:15.458 --> 11:17.834
<i>remains onboard</i>

11:17.875 --> 11:20.834
<i>to continue</i>

11:17.875 --> 11:20.834
<i>tactical preparations.</i>

11:20.875 --> 11:23.166
I've also ordered

11:20.875 --> 11:23.166
a standing Yellow Alert.

11:23.208 --> 11:25.417
All Federation-allied outposts

11:23.208 --> 11:25.417
have been warned.

11:25.458 --> 11:28.250
Ops will continue to monitor

11:25.458 --> 11:28.250
long-range sensors.

11:28.291 --> 11:30.083
I've assigned Data,

11:28.291 --> 11:30.083
La Forge and Mr. Crusher

11:30.125 --> 11:31.291
to work

11:30.125 --> 11:31.291
with Commander Shelby.

11:31.333 --> 11:32.333
Good.

11:32.375 --> 11:34.250
You've covered all the bases.

11:35.375 --> 11:38.500
What's your impression

11:35.375 --> 11:38.500
of Shelby?

11:38.542 --> 11:40.125
She knows her stuff.

11:40.166 --> 11:41.375
She has your

11:40.166 --> 11:41.375
full confidence?

11:41.417 --> 11:43.917
Well, I think she

11:41.417 --> 11:43.917
needs supervision.

11:43.959 --> 11:46.125
She takes the initiative

11:43.959 --> 11:46.125
a little too easily--

11:46.166 --> 11:47.083
sometimes with risks.

11:47.125 --> 11:48.667
(<i> tsking</i> )

11:48.709 --> 11:50.750
Sounds like a young

11:48.709 --> 11:50.750
Lieutenant Commander

11:50.792 --> 11:52.291
I recruited

11:50.792 --> 11:52.291
as a First Officer.

11:52.333 --> 11:53.917
Perhaps.

11:56.458 --> 11:58.166
Will...

12:00.542 --> 12:03.166
what the hell are you

12:00.542 --> 12:03.166
still doing here?

12:03.208 --> 12:04.500
Sir?

12:04.542 --> 12:07.083
You've been offered

12:04.542 --> 12:07.083
the<i> Melbourne.</i>

12:07.125 --> 12:09.959
I've decided not to pursue

12:07.125 --> 12:09.959
that commission at this time.

12:10.041 --> 12:12.375
She's a fine ship, Will.

12:12.417 --> 12:15.417
Yes, but she's not the

12:12.417 --> 12:15.417
<i>Enterprise.</i>

12:15.458 --> 12:20.250
With all due respect, sir,

12:15.458 --> 12:20.250
you need me, particularly now.

12:20.291 --> 12:25.166
Indeed. Starfleet needs

12:20.291 --> 12:25.166
good Captains, particularly now.

12:25.208 --> 12:26.917
Reconsider your decision.

12:28.041 --> 12:30.166
Are you telling me to leave,

12:28.041 --> 12:30.166
Captain?

12:30.208 --> 12:34.917
I'm asking you to look

12:30.208 --> 12:34.917
at your career objectively.

12:34.959 --> 12:40.917
Will, you're ready

12:34.959 --> 12:40.917
to work without a net.

12:40.959 --> 12:43.500
You're ready

12:40.959 --> 12:43.500
to take command

12:43.542 --> 12:46.208
and, you know,<i> Enterprise</i>

12:46.250 --> 12:49.500
will go along

12:46.250 --> 12:49.500
just fine without you.

12:49.542 --> 12:51.625
What am I still doing here?

12:51.667 --> 12:54.792
Deanna, I pushed myself

12:51.667 --> 12:54.792
hard to get this far.

12:54.834 --> 12:57.792
I... I sacrificed a lot.

12:57.834 --> 12:59.333
I always said I wanted

12:57.834 --> 12:59.333
my own command

12:59.375 --> 13:02.125
and yet... something's

12:59.375 --> 13:02.125
holding me back.

13:02.166 --> 13:04.083
Is it wrong for me

13:02.166 --> 13:04.083
to want to stay?

13:04.125 --> 13:05.667
What do you think?

13:07.208 --> 13:09.375
(<i> sighs</i> )

13:11.291 --> 13:14.250
Maybe I'm just afraid

13:11.291 --> 13:14.250
of the big chair.

13:14.291 --> 13:16.959
I don't think so.

13:17.000 --> 13:19.166
The Captain says

13:19.208 --> 13:21.542
Shelby reminds him

13:19.208 --> 13:21.542
of the way that I used to be

13:21.583 --> 13:22.959
and he's right.

13:23.000 --> 13:25.625
She comes in here

13:23.000 --> 13:25.625
full of drive and ambition.

13:25.667 --> 13:28.000
Impatient, taking risks.

13:28.041 --> 13:30.333
