25:00.959 --> 25:03.125
power transfers

25:03.166 --> 25:04.667
to the deflector

25:03.166 --> 25:04.667
dish, Commander.

25:03.166 --> 25:04.667
How long?

25:04.709 --> 25:07.458
Better part

25:04.709 --> 25:07.458
of a day.

25:07.500 --> 25:09.166
She gets a full head

25:07.500 --> 25:09.166
of steam, doesn't she?

25:09.208 --> 25:11.375
Mm-hmm. She's a formidable

25:09.208 --> 25:11.375
presence, to say the least

25:11.417 --> 25:13.625
but I'm convinced she can

25:11.417 --> 25:13.625
help us here, Commander.

25:13.667 --> 25:14.709
I am, too.

25:14.750 --> 25:15.834
Don't worry about it.

25:15.875 --> 25:17.500
I can handle Shelby.

25:20.333 --> 25:22.291
(<i> door chimes</i> )

25:20.333 --> 25:22.291
Come.

25:26.542 --> 25:29.166
Come in, Number One.

25:29.208 --> 25:30.792
Commander Shelby

25:29.208 --> 25:30.792
was just telling me

25:30.834 --> 25:35.417
of your... concerns

25:30.834 --> 25:35.417
about her plan.

25:35.458 --> 25:36.834
I'm sorry if she

25:35.458 --> 25:36.834
troubled you, sir.

25:36.875 --> 25:38.583
I have already

25:36.875 --> 25:38.583
informed her...

25:38.625 --> 25:40.208
PICARD:

25:38.625 --> 25:40.208
Yes, I entirely agree

25:38.625 --> 25:40.208
with you, Number One.

25:40.250 --> 25:42.667
It's not the time.

25:42.709 --> 25:44.709
But the time may come

25:44.750 --> 25:47.834
when we will be required

25:44.750 --> 25:47.834
to take greater risks.

25:47.875 --> 25:52.375
I want you to consider her plan

25:47.875 --> 25:52.375
as a fall-back position.

25:52.417 --> 25:54.166
Make the necessary preparations.

25:54.208 --> 25:56.291
Very good, sir.

26:05.542 --> 26:07.375
Deck eight,

26:05.542 --> 26:07.375
Battle Bridge.

26:07.417 --> 26:08.875
Halt.

26:08.917 --> 26:12.583
Commander, you and I need

26:08.917 --> 26:12.583
to have a conversation.

26:12.625 --> 26:15.667
You never ordered me not to

26:12.625 --> 26:15.667
discuss this with the Captain.

26:15.709 --> 26:17.667
You disagree with me--

26:15.709 --> 26:17.667
fine.

26:17.709 --> 26:20.041
You need to take it

26:17.709 --> 26:20.041
to the Captain-- fine.

26:20.083 --> 26:21.333
Through me.

26:21.375 --> 26:24.166
You do an end run

26:21.375 --> 26:24.166
around me again

26:24.208 --> 26:25.667
I'll snap you back so hard

26:25.709 --> 26:27.625
you'll think you're

26:25.709 --> 26:27.625
a first-year cadet again.

26:27.667 --> 26:29.959
May I speak frankly, sir?

26:30.000 --> 26:31.792
By all means.

26:31.834 --> 26:33.667
You're in my way.

26:33.709 --> 26:36.583
Really.

26:36.625 --> 26:38.667
How terrible for you.

26:38.709 --> 26:40.875
All you know how to do

26:38.709 --> 26:40.875
is play it safe.

26:40.917 --> 26:43.000
I suppose that's why

26:40.917 --> 26:43.000
someone like you

26:43.041 --> 26:44.583
sits in the shadow

26:43.041 --> 26:44.583
of a great man

26:44.625 --> 26:45.709
for as long as you have

26:45.750 --> 26:47.959
passing up one command

26:45.750 --> 26:47.959
after another.

26:48.000 --> 26:50.667
Proceed to deck eight.

26:50.709 --> 26:53.417
When it comes to this

26:50.709 --> 26:53.417
ship and this crew

26:53.458 --> 26:56.625
you're damned right

26:53.458 --> 26:56.625
I play it safe.

26:56.667 --> 26:59.583
If you can't make

26:56.667 --> 26:59.583
the big decisions, Commander

26:59.625 --> 27:02.542
I suggest you make room

26:59.625 --> 27:02.542
for someone who can.

27:15.917 --> 27:18.625
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

27:15.917 --> 27:18.625
<i>Stardate 43996.2.</i>

27:18.667 --> 27:20.834
<i>The</i> Enterprise<i> remains</i>

27:18.667 --> 27:20.834
<i>concealed in the dust cloud.</i>

27:20.875 --> 27:24.125
<i>And, to my surprise, the Borg</i>

27:20.875 --> 27:24.125
<i>have maintained their position</i>

27:24.166 --> 27:25.917
<i>waiting for us</i>

27:24.166 --> 27:25.917
<i>to come out of hiding.</i>

27:25.959 --> 27:27.542
<i>I have no explanation</i>

27:27.583 --> 27:30.333
<i>for their special interest</i>

27:27.583 --> 27:30.333
<i>in me or this ship.</i>

27:30.375 --> 27:32.375
<i>We continue to prepare</i>

27:30.375 --> 27:32.375
<i>our defenses</i>

27:32.417 --> 27:33.917
<i>for the inevitable</i>

27:32.417 --> 27:33.917
<i>confrontation</i>

27:33.959 --> 27:36.834
<i>but, I must admit,</i>

27:33.959 --> 27:36.834
<i>on this night</i>

27:36.875 --> 27:38.792
<i>I contemplate</i>

27:36.875 --> 27:38.792
<i>the distinct possibility</i>

27:38.834 --> 27:41.417
<i>that no defense may be adequate</i>

27:38.834 --> 27:41.417
<i>against this enemy.</i>

27:41.458 --> 27:42.875
Captain.

28:04.000 --> 28:07.709
Trouble sleeping?

28:07.750 --> 28:11.458
It's something of a tradition,

28:07.750 --> 28:11.458
Guinan--

28:11.500 --> 28:14.959
Captain touring the ship

28:11.500 --> 28:14.959
before a battle.

28:15.000 --> 28:16.667
Oh.

28:16.709 --> 28:18.542
Before a<i> hopeless</i> battle

28:18.583 --> 28:21.166
if I remember

28:18.583 --> 28:21.166
the tradition correctly.

28:21.208 --> 28:23.125
Not necessarily.

28:23.166 --> 28:25.500
Nelson toured the HMS<i> Victory</i>

28:23.166 --> 28:25.500
<i>before Trafalgar.</i>

28:25.542 --> 28:29.834
Yes, but Nelson never returned

28:25.542 --> 28:29.834
from Trafalgar, did he?

28:29.875 --> 28:33.792
No, but the battle

28:29.875 --> 28:33.792
was won.

28:33.834 --> 28:37.750
Do you expect this

28:33.834 --> 28:37.750
battle to be won?

28:37.792 --> 28:41.250
We may yet prevail.

28:41.291 --> 28:44.583
That's... a conceit.

28:44.625 --> 28:47.875
But... it's a healthy one.

28:47.917 --> 28:50.458
I wonder if

28:47.917 --> 28:50.458
the Emperor Honorius

28:50.500 --> 28:53.875
watching the Visigoths

28:50.500 --> 28:53.875
coming over the seventh hill

28:53.917 --> 29:00.667
truly realized that the Roman

28:53.917 --> 29:00.667
Empire was about to fall.

29:00.709 --> 29:05.208
This is just another page

29:00.709 --> 29:05.208
in history, isn't it?

29:05.250 --> 29:08.875
Will this be the end

29:05.250 --> 29:08.875
of<i> our</i> civilization?

29:08.917 --> 29:11.375
Turn the page.

29:14.291 --> 29:16.583
This isn't the end.

29:16.625 --> 29:20.959
You say that

29:16.625 --> 29:20.959
with remarkable assuredness.

29:21.000 --> 29:23.166
With experience.

29:23.208 --> 29:25.458
When the Borg destroyed

29:23.208 --> 29:25.458
my world

29:25.500 --> 29:29.291
my people were scattered

29:25.500 --> 29:29.291
throughout the universe.

29:29.333 --> 29:31.208
We survived.

29:31.250 --> 29:34.166
As will humanity survive.

29:34.208 --> 29:36.750
As long as there's

29:34.208 --> 29:36.750
a handful of you

29:36.792 --> 29:38.500
to keep

29:36.792 --> 29:38.500
the spirit alive

29:38.542 --> 29:40.625
you<i> will</i> prevail.

29:40.667 --> 29:43.166
Even if it takes a millennium.

29:44.000 --> 29:46.917
(<i> explosion</i> )

29:46.959 --> 29:50.542
WORF:

29:46.959 --> 29:50.542
Captain Picard,

29:46.959 --> 29:50.542
report to the Bridge.

29:50.583 --> 29:53.208
I'm on my way, Lieutenant.

30:11.333 --> 30:14.709
They're some sort

30:11.333 --> 30:14.709
of magnetometric-guided charges.

30:19.375 --> 30:20.750
Status of shields?

30:20.792 --> 30:22.709
WORF:

30:20.792 --> 30:22.709
Back to 48%, Captain.

30:22.750 --> 30:25.125
Mr. La Forge, I may have

30:22.750 --> 30:25.125
to take us out of the nebula.

30:25.166 --> 30:26.875
I want all the power

30:25.166 --> 30:26.875
you can give me.

30:26.917 --> 30:28.250
Engines are ready, Captain.

30:28.291 --> 30:29.792
Recommend you adjust

30:28.291 --> 30:29.792
shield harmonics

30:29.834 --> 30:32.375
to favor the upper EM band

30:29.834 --> 30:32.375
when you proceed.

30:32.417 --> 30:34.208
Acknowledged.

30:35.625 --> 30:37.166
Direct hit, deck nine.

30:37.208 --> 30:38.583
Damage report.

30:38.625 --> 30:40.875
Structural latching system

30:38.625 --> 30:40.875
integrity breached.

30:40.917 --> 30:42.500
Prepare to take us

30:40.917 --> 30:42.500
out of here, Number One.

30:42.542 --> 30:43.625
Fire up the engines.

30:43.667 --> 30:45.125
Half impulse till we

30:43.667 --> 30:45.125
clear the nebula

30:45.166 --> 30:46.667
then punch it up

30:45.166 --> 30:46.667
to warp nine.

30:46.709 --> 30:48.959
Ready phasers, load

30:46.709 --> 30:48.959
forward torpedo bays.

30:49.000 --> 30:50.750
Engage.

30:58.333 --> 31:00.041
Borg tractor beam

30:58.333 --> 31:00.041
is attempting to lock on.

31:00.083 --> 31:01.291
Fire at will.

31:01.333 --> 31:02.834
Continue rotating

31:01.333 --> 31:02.834
shield frequency.

31:02.875 --> 31:03.959
(<i> console beeping</i> )

31:04.000 --> 31:05.291
Shields failing.

31:06.417 --> 31:07.959
(<i> insistent beeping</i> )

31:08.000 --> 31:09.875
Tractor beam<i> has</i> locked on.

31:29.625 --> 31:33.250
It's no use.

31:29.625 --> 31:33.250
They've already adapted

31:29.625 --> 31:33.250
to the new frequencies.

31:34.333 --> 31:35.500
(<i> grunts</i> )

32:01.709 --> 32:03.333
The Borg ship

32:01.709 --> 32:03.333
is disengaging.

32:03.375 --> 32:04.792
Leaving at

32:03.375 --> 32:04.792
warp speed.

32:04.834 --> 32:07.041
Maintain pursuit.

32:09.291 --> 32:14.709
Borg vessel has reached

32:09.291 --> 32:14.709
warp nine, 9.4, 9.6.

32:14.750 --> 32:15.750
Stay with them.

32:15.792 --> 32:17.125
Riker to O'Brien.

32:17.166 --> 32:18.208
Can you get a fix

32:17.166 --> 32:18.208
on the Captain?

32:18.250 --> 32:19.375
Negative, sir.

32:19.417 --> 32:20.667
There's some kind

32:19.417 --> 32:20.667
of interference.

32:20.709 --> 32:22.667
I can't lock in on his signal.

32:22.709 --> 32:25.083
Senior officers,

32:22.709 --> 32:25.083
report to the Bridge.

32:25.125 --> 32:27.000
Sir, the coordinates

32:25.125 --> 32:27.000
they have set--

32:27.041 --> 32:28.417
they are on a

32:27.041 --> 32:28.417
direct course

32:28.458 --> 32:34.625
to Sector 001--

32:28.458 --> 32:34.625
the Terran system.

32:34.667 --> 32:36.709
Earth.

33:04.959 --> 33:07.083
BORG VOICES:

33:04.959 --> 33:07.083
Captain Jean-Luc Picard

33:07.125 --> 33:09.709
you lead the strongest ship

33:07.125 --> 33:09.709
of the Federation fleet.

33:09.750 --> 33:11.834
You speak for your people.

33:11.875 --> 33:13.917
I have nothing to say to you

33:13.959 --> 33:17.750
and I will resist you

33:13.959 --> 33:17.750
with my last ounce of strength.

33:17.792 --> 33:19.166
Strength is irrelevant.

33:19.208 --> 33:20.875
Resistance is futile.

33:20.917 --> 33:22.875
We wish to improve ourselves.

33:22.917 --> 33:24.667
We will add your biological

33:24.709 --> 33:26.875
and technological

33:24.709 --> 33:26.875
distinctiveness to our own.

33:26.917 --> 33:30.375
Your culture will adapt

33:26.917 --> 33:30.375
to service ours.

33:30.417 --> 33:32.250
Impossible.

33:32.291 --> 33:35.917
My culture is based on freedom

33:32.291 --> 33:35.917
and self-determination.

33:35.959 --> 33:37.709
Freedom is irrelevant.

33:37.750 --> 33:39.750
Self-determination

33:37.750 --> 33:39.750
is irrelevant.

33:39.792 --> 33:41.667
You must comply.

33:41.709 --> 33:43.834
We would rather die.

33:43.875 --> 33:45.792
Death is irrelevant.

33:45.834 --> 33:48.834
Your archaic cultures

33:45.834 --> 33:48.834
are authority driven.

33:48.875 --> 33:51.792
To facilitate our introduction

33:48.875 --> 33:51.792
into your societies

33:51.834 --> 33:54.917
it has been decided that a human

33:51.834 --> 33:54.917
voice will speak for us

33:54.959 --> 33:56.250
in all communications.

33:56.291 --> 33:59.458
You have been chosen

33:56.291 --> 33:59.458
to be that voice.

34:06.250 --> 34:07.792
WORF:

34:06.250 --> 34:07.792
Commander, they

34:06.250 --> 34:07.792
are leading us

34:07.834 --> 34:09.750
into the heart

34:07.834 --> 34:09.750
of our own defenses.

34:09.792 --> 34:11.208
Yeah, well, so far,

34:09.792 --> 34:11.208
they haven't had

34:11.250 --> 34:13.542
much of a reason

34:11.250 --> 34:13.542
to worry about our defenses.

34:13.583 --> 34:16.333
Commander, if the Borg

34:13.583 --> 34:16.333
stay at warp 9.6

34:16.375 --> 34:17.709
we'll be forced

34:16.375 --> 34:17.709
to discontinue pursuit

34:17.750 --> 34:19.417
and power down

34:17.750 --> 34:19.417
in less than three hours.

34:19.458 --> 34:21.166
Two hours,

34:19.458 --> 34:21.166
40 minutes,

34:19.458 --> 34:21.166
three seconds.

34:21.208 --> 34:22.792
How long before

34:21.208 --> 34:22.792
the deflector's ready?

34:22.834 --> 34:24.875
We're close, a few hours maybe.

34:24.917 --> 34:27.083
I know-- I'll get it done

34:24.917 --> 34:27.083
in two somehow

34:27.125 --> 34:28.750
but, Commander, I'm going

34:27.125 --> 34:28.750
to need serious power

34:28.792 --> 34:30.875
from the warp engines

34:28.792 --> 34:30.875
to make this weapon work.

34:30.917 --> 34:32.083
So far, we're using

34:30.917 --> 34:32.083
everything we've got

34:32.125 --> 34:33.500
just to keep up with them.

34:33.542 --> 34:36.500
Sir, we've got to get that ship

34:33.542 --> 34:36.500
down to impulse.

34:36.542 --> 34:40.333
I'm leading an away team over

34:36.542 --> 34:40.333
there to get the Captain back.

34:40.375 --> 34:41.917
We'll find a way

34:40.375 --> 34:41.917
to get them out of warp.

34:41.959 --> 34:44.166
Ensign Crusher, you continue

34:41.959 --> 34:44.166
to assist Mr. La Forge.

34:44.208 --> 34:45.834
Commander Shelby,

34:44.208 --> 34:45.834
you'll take the Bridge

34:45.875 --> 34:47.000
and coordinate

34:45.875 --> 34:47.000
with Starfleet.

34:47.041 --> 34:48.959
Data, Worf, Doctor,

34:47.041 --> 34:48.959
you're with me.

34:49.000 --> 34:50.125
Excuse me, sir.

34:50.166 --> 34:51.250
With my knowledge

34:50.166 --> 34:51.250
of the Borg...

34:51.291 --> 34:53.166
Those are my

34:51.291 --> 34:53.166
orders, Commander!

34:53.208 --> 34:55.041
TROI:

34:53.208 --> 34:55.041
Commander Riker

34:55.083 --> 35:00.041
it is inappropriate for you

34:55.083 --> 35:00.041
to lead the away team.

35:00.083 --> 35:02.125
Until the return

35:00.083 --> 35:02.125
of Captain Picard

35:02.166 --> 35:04.333
you are in command

35:02.166 --> 35:04.333
of the<i> Enterprise.</i>

35:04.375 --> 35:05.792
We're in

35:04.375 --> 35:05.792
a state of war

35:05.834 --> 35:08.291
and your place

35:05.834 --> 35:08.291
is on the Bridge.

35:13.750 --> 35:14.917
Commander Shelby

35:14.959 --> 35:16.709
you'll lead

35:14.959 --> 35:16.709
the away team.

35:16.750 --> 35:19.083
Make it so.

35:30.291 --> 35:33.542
<i>First Officer's Log,</i>

35:30.291 --> 35:33.542
<i>Stardate 43998.5.</i>

35:33.583 --> 35:35.000
<i>Our pursuit of the Borg</i>

35:35.041 --> 35:36.542
<i>continues on a course</i>

35:35.041 --> 35:36.542
<i>that will take us</i>

35:36.583 --> 35:38.458
<i>to the very core</i>

35:36.583 --> 35:38.458
<i>of the Federation.</i>

35:38.500 --> 35:41.500
<i>The devastation they could</i>

35:38.500 --> 35:41.500
<i>bring is beyond imagination.</i>

35:41.542 --> 35:44.667
These phasers

35:41.542 --> 35:44.667
have been retuned.

35:44.709 --> 35:47.625
Each has a different frequency

35:44.709 --> 35:47.625
spanning the upper EM band.

35:47.667 --> 35:49.583
All right, a reminder--

35:47.667 --> 35:49.583
we only get to use

35:49.625 --> 35:51.250
each of these once,

35:49.625 --> 35:51.250
maybe twice

35:51.291 --> 35:52.875
before the Borg

35:51.291 --> 35:52.875
learn to adapt.

35:52.917 --> 35:54.917
Don't fire

35:52.917 --> 35:54.917
until you have to.

35:54.959 --> 35:57.041
What kind of resistance

35:54.959 --> 35:57.041
should we expect?

35:57.083 --> 36:00.166
At our first encounter,

35:57.083 --> 36:00.166
the Borg virtually ignored us

36:00.208 --> 36:01.834
when we beamed aboard

36:00.208 --> 36:01.834
their vessel.

36:01.875 --> 36:04.375
Clearly, they did not consider

36:01.875 --> 36:04.375
our being there a threat.

36:04.417 --> 36:05.750
That may change, however

36:05.792 --> 36:08.709
if we start interfering

36:05.792 --> 36:08.709
with their plans.

36:15.750 --> 36:17.125
Shelby to Bridge.

36:17.166 --> 36:18.333
Away team ready.

36:18.375 --> 36:19.750
We've got 58 minutes

36:19.792 --> 36:21.625
before we have to power down

36:19.792 --> 36:21.625
and disengage.

36:21.667 --> 36:22.709
Understood.

36:22.750 --> 36:23.792
Proceed. Commander?

36:23.834 --> 36:26.583
No unnecessary risks.

36:23.834 --> 36:26.583
Clear?

36:26.625 --> 36:27.667
Very clear, sir.

36:27.709 --> 36:29.291
Shelby out.

36:29.333 --> 36:32.083
We've matched warp velocity

36:29.333 --> 36:32.083
for transport, Commander.

36:32.125 --> 36:33.625
Energize.

36:49.709 --> 36:51.875
WORF:

36:49.709 --> 36:51.875
Tricorder functions minimal.

36:51.917 --> 36:53.542
Any signs of human life?

36:53.583 --> 36:55.792
Inconclusive.

37:27.500 --> 37:28.583
Look at this.

37:28.625 --> 37:30.917
This is extraordinary.

37:32.917 --> 37:34.125
Those appear to be

37:34.166 --> 37:37.333
some kind of power

37:34.166 --> 37:37.333
waveguide conduits

37:37.375 --> 37:39.583
which allow them

37:37.375 --> 37:39.583
to work collectively

37:39.625 --> 37:41.417
as they perform

37:39.625 --> 37:41.417
ship functions.

37:41.458 --> 37:43.792
There's no way to take

37:41.458 --> 37:43.792
out enough of these

37:43.834 --> 37:45.041
to disable them.

37:45.083 --> 37:46.291
What if we

37:45.083 --> 37:46.291
look at this

37:46.333 --> 37:48.834
from the mosquito's

37:46.333 --> 37:48.834
point of view?

37:48.875 --> 37:50.667
Interesting metaphor, Doctor.

37:50.709 --> 37:52.208
What is your idea?

37:52.250 --> 37:55.000
If we sting them

37:52.250 --> 37:55.000
in a tender spot

37:55.041 --> 37:58.792
they might stop for

37:55.041 --> 37:58.792
a minute to scratch.

38:13.959 --> 38:16.041
Distribution

38:13.959 --> 38:16.041
nodes.

38:16.083 --> 38:19.750
SHELBY:

38:16.083 --> 38:19.750
If we take out a few of these,

38:16.083 --> 38:19.750
it just might make them scratch.

38:19.792 --> 38:21.667
The Captain's

38:19.792 --> 38:21.667
communicator--

38:21.709 --> 38:23.166
it is still activated.

38:23.208 --> 38:24.375
Crusher to Picard.

38:24.417 --> 38:25.583
Can you hear me?

38:25.625 --> 38:29.375
Can you locate it, Worf?

38:29.417 --> 38:31.041
This way.

38:34.709 --> 38:37.792
I strongly recommend redeploying

38:34.709 --> 38:37.792
all available defenses

38:37.834 --> 38:39.291
to protect Sector 001, Admiral.

38:39.333 --> 38:43.208
We're moving to intercept

38:39.333 --> 38:43.208
at Wolf 359.

38:43.250 --> 38:44.875
We'll make our stand there.

38:44.917 --> 38:47.250
How much longer can you

38:44.917 --> 38:47.250
maintain pursuit?

38:47.291 --> 38:49.875
22 minutes if they stay

38:47.291 --> 38:49.875
at their current speed.

38:49.917 --> 38:51.750
If we can't bring them

38:49.917 --> 38:51.750
out of warp

38:51.792 --> 38:53.917
we'll do as much damage

38:51.792 --> 38:53.917
as we can

38:53.959 --> 38:56.375
before we have to disengage.

38:56.417 --> 38:58.250
Picard?

38:59.375 --> 39:01.458
Nothing yet, sir.

39:02.333 --> 39:05.375
(<i> tricorder beeping</i> )

39:05.417 --> 39:08.083
(<i> beeping faster</i> )

39:08.125 --> 39:09.792
In here.

39:33.166 --> 39:34.959
Shelby to<i> Enterprise.</i>

39:35.000 --> 39:36.166
Go ahead.

39:36.208 --> 39:37.417
We've found

39:36.208 --> 39:37.417
the Captain's uniform

39:37.458 --> 39:38.709
and his communicator.

39:38.750 --> 39:41.291
We're resuming our search.

39:41.333 --> 39:43.166
Stand by, Commander.

39:43.208 --> 39:44.417
We're in business.

39:44.458 --> 39:46.375
It'll burn out

39:44.458 --> 39:46.375
the main deflector

39:46.417 --> 39:48.083
but it'll be one

39:46.417 --> 39:48.083
hell of a bang.

39:48.125 --> 39:49.208
Radiation danger?

39:49.250 --> 39:50.750
We're going to have

39:49.250 --> 39:50.750
to evacuate

39:50.792 --> 39:52.583
the entire forward half

39:50.792 --> 39:52.583
of the secondary hull

39:52.625 --> 39:54.000
and the lower three

39:52.625 --> 39:54.000
decks of the saucer.

39:54.041 --> 39:56.291
I'll see to that.

39:56.333 --> 39:58.000
Commander Shelby

39:58.041 --> 40:00.250
we have only 17 minutes

39:58.041 --> 40:00.250
of warp power left.

40:00.291 --> 40:03.083
Do whatever you can

40:00.291 --> 40:03.083
to get them out of warp.

40:03.125 --> 40:04.375
Acknowledged.

40:04.417 --> 40:06.291
Shelby out.

40:11.583 --> 40:13.500
Let's take out some

40:11.583 --> 40:13.500
of these distribution nodes

40:13.542 --> 40:15.667
and see what happens.

40:49.125 --> 40:50.667
Sir, they've done it.

40:50.709 --> 40:52.000
The Borg ship

40:50.709 --> 40:52.000
is dropping out of warp.

40:52.041 --> 40:54.125
Go to impulse.

40:54.166 --> 40:55.375
Aye, sir.

40:55.417 --> 40:57.709
Diverting warp power

40:55.417 --> 40:57.709
to main deflector.

40:57.750 --> 41:00.125
Move us to within

40:57.750 --> 41:00.125
40,000 kilometers

41:00.166 --> 41:01.500
and match velocity.

41:01.542 --> 41:03.000
Commence arming sequence.

41:03.041 --> 41:06.458
Increase deflector modulation

41:03.041 --> 41:06.458
to upper frequency band.

41:28.792 --> 41:30.000
Shelby to<i> Enterprise.</i>

41:30.041 --> 41:31.208
Encountering resistance.

41:31.250 --> 41:33.125
Prepare to beam us

41:31.250 --> 41:33.125
back on my signal.

41:50.709 --> 41:53.792
SHELBY:

41:50.709 --> 41:53.792
They're adapting

41:50.709 --> 41:53.792
to the frequencies.

41:57.166 --> 41:58.875
Jean-Luc.

42:04.917 --> 42:06.542
Captain!

42:06.583 --> 42:08.375
(<i> gasps</i> )

42:16.542 --> 42:18.667
(<i> grunts</i> )

42:18.709 --> 42:20.375
<i>Enterprise,</i> get us out of here.

42:38.875 --> 42:40.083
The Captain?

42:40.125 --> 42:42.208
We were unable to

42:40.125 --> 42:42.208
retrieve him, sir.

42:42.250 --> 42:44.291
The Captain has been

42:42.250 --> 42:44.291
altered by the Borg.

42:44.333 --> 42:45.458
Altered?

42:45.500 --> 42:49.000
He<i> is</i> a Borg.

42:49.041 --> 42:51.458
We'll go back.

42:49.041 --> 42:51.458
I need more people.

42:51.500 --> 42:52.792
We need to retune

42:51.500 --> 42:52.792
the phasers again.

42:52.834 --> 42:54.166
We'll get him

42:52.834 --> 42:54.166
out of there.

42:54.208 --> 42:55.709
LA FORGE:

42:54.208 --> 42:55.709
Commander.

42:55.750 --> 42:58.000
Reading subspace field

42:55.750 --> 42:58.000
fluctuations from within

42:58.041 --> 42:58.959
the Borg ship.

42:59.000 --> 43:00.083
Looks like

42:59.000 --> 43:00.083
they're...

43:00.125 --> 43:01.834
regenerating-- restoring power.

43:01.875 --> 43:04.208
They could be capable

43:01.875 --> 43:04.208
of warp any minute.

43:04.250 --> 43:06.166
Is the deflector ready?

43:06.208 --> 43:08.083
It's ready.

43:08.125 --> 43:11.291
Will, he's alive.

43:08.125 --> 43:11.291
If we could get him

43:08.125 --> 43:11.291
back to the ship

43:11.333 --> 43:13.583
I might be able

43:11.333 --> 43:13.583
to restore...

43:11.333 --> 43:13.583
This is our only chance

43:11.333 --> 43:13.583
to destroy them.

43:13.625 --> 43:16.709
If they get back into warp,

43:13.625 --> 43:16.709
our weapon is useless.

43:16.750 --> 43:18.750
We'll sabotage them again

43:16.750 --> 43:18.750
if we have to.

43:18.792 --> 43:20.458
We can't maintain power.

43:20.500 --> 43:22.583
We don't have the time.

43:20.500 --> 43:22.583
Prepare to fire.

43:22.625 --> 43:24.041
At least consult

43:22.625 --> 43:24.041
with Starfleet Command.

43:24.083 --> 43:25.834
Get Admiral Hanson

43:24.083 --> 43:25.834
on subspace.

43:25.875 --> 43:27.458
Belay that order, Lieutenant.

43:27.500 --> 43:28.542
There's no time.

43:29.667 --> 43:32.583
Sir, we are being hailed

43:29.667 --> 43:32.583
by the Borg.

43:33.625 --> 43:35.375
On screen.

43:52.625 --> 43:56.625
I am Locutus of Borg.

43:56.667 --> 44:00.083
Resistance is futile.

44:00.125 --> 44:06.291
Your life, as it has been,

44:00.125 --> 44:06.291
is over.

44:06.333 --> 44:08.625
From this time forward,

44:08.667 --> 44:13.375
you will service<i> us.</i>

44:23.375 --> 44:28.000
Mr. Worf... fire.
